<p>
<s snum=65>Mr. Robards- Jenny was the only person she knew of in the Mt. Pleasant neighborhood who called him that- was kind but too easygoing.</s>
<s snum=66>It didn't bother him for everybody from the blacksmith to the preacher to say, ``Howdy, Miss Jenny'', adding a careless ``Roy'', but it did her.</s>
</p>
<p>
<s snum=67>He could put a stop to it, she told him again and again.</s>
<s snum=68>Simply call Mr. Whipsnade Oscar, and Dr. Dunne P.G., and C'un Major Frank.</s>
<s snum=69>Mr. Robards laughed, said he'd feel a damn fool, plain-out couldn't do that even to please her.</s>
</p>
<p>
<s snum=70>``You could try.</s>
